<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-09-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-09-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1706" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1706">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 511.4Al/1514a.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to Minister <persName type="to">Van
                                    Dyke</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-23">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 23, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>200. Ascertain and cable what countries have deposited with Netherlands
                            Government their ratifications of International Opium Convention in
                            accordance with protocol of Second Conference, and what is prospect of
                            deposit of ratifications by other governments; also whether there is any
                            likelihood of any of the governments who have deposited ratifications
                            effectuating the convention as have the United States, China, and the
                            Netherlands.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>